Description. Habitus (
Fig. 65
). TL: 2.1–2.5 mm ; MW: 1.0– 1.3 mm ( holotype : TL: 2.3 mm ; MW: 1.2 mm ); A- TL: 2.3 mm ; A-MW: 1.2 mm (NUM: 67 exs); body elongate, drop-shaped, elytra often markedly sinuate subapically.

Structures and sculpture . Head smooth, shiny, with fine microreticulation of rounded cells. Pronotum with microreticulation as on head, shiny, with faint iridescence. Few scattered punctures mostly along fore and hind margins. Elytra with subapical sinuation quite pronounced; smooth with quite impressed reticulation and intense iridescence. Prosternal process (
Figs 29–31
) slightly elevated, rounded at tip. Lobes of metacoxal processes rounded in both sexes (
Fig. 40
).
